 the most common cause of Cushing\u0027s syndrome?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Pituitary adenoma","Ectopic adrenocorticotropic hormone production","Exogenous glucocorticoid therapy","Adrenocortical tumour","Adrenal hyperplasia"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical features described are typical of Cushing\u0027s syndrome with \u003Cstrong\u003Eexogenous glucocorticoid therapy\u003C/strong\u003E being the most common cause. Among cases of endogenous Cushing\u0027s syndrome, \u003Cstrong\u003Epituitary adenomas\u003C/strong\u003E (Cushing\u0027s disease) are most common, accounting for about 70% of cases.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEctopic adrenocorticotropic hormone production\u003C/strong\u003E, typically from small cell lung cancer or carcinoid tumours account for about 10% of endogenous cases. \u003Cstrong\u003EAdrenocortical tumours\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eadrenal hyperplasia\u003C/strong\u003E are less common causes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Exogenous glucocorticoid therapy is the most common cause of Cushing\u0027s syndrome.","Classic features of Cushing\u0027s syndrome include central obesity, moon face, buffalo hump, and psychological disturbances.","Endogenous Cushing\u0027s syndrome is most commonly caused by pituitary adenomas (Cushing\u0027s disease)."],"references":["Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Pre